  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Two animals, one wheel</p>
    <h1>See how <em>your two animals</em> read one another.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Enter two dates of birth. The Oracle scores the pair across the four Chinese systems and the Western elements, names the tier, and tells you honestly what the bond can carry. Compatibility supports a relationship. It does not make one.</p>

    <!-- MATCH FORM -->
    <div class="reader" id="matchPanel">
      <h3>Test the match</h3>
      <p class="dim">Nothing is sent anywhere. The score is drawn in your browser.</p>
      <form id="matchForm">
        <div class="matchGrid">
          <div>
            <label for="mDateA">You</label>
            <input type="date" id="mDateA" required min="1940-01-01" max="2032-12-31" aria-label="Your date of birth">
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="mDateB">Them</label>
            <input type="date" id="mDateB" required min="1940-01-01" max="2032-12-31" aria-label="Their date of birth">
          </div>
          <button class="btn" type="submit">Test the match</button>
        </div>
        <p class="msg" id="matchMsg"></p>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RESULT -->
  <div id="matchResult" aria-live="polite"></div>

  <!-- HOW THE SCORE IS BUILT -->
  <section class="band" id="method">
    <p class="eyebrow">Why the score is earned</p>
    <h2>What the Oracle weighs</h2>
    <p class="lede">The pair is read across four Chinese relationships and the Western element logic. Each one moves the score, so the tier reflects a real structure rather than a guess.</p>

    <div class="methodGrid">
      <div class="methodCard">
        <h3>Trines, San He</h3>
        <p>The twelve animals fall into four triangles of three. Animals in the same triangle share a rhythm and a way of moving through the world. A match inside a trine earns the strongest natural lift, because the pull is steady and needs little translation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="methodCard">
        <h3>Secret friends, Liu He</h3>
        <p>Six pairs are bound as secret friends, animals that quietly complete and steady each other. The fit is easy and balancing in a way that is felt more than explained, and the Oracle weights it as highly as a trine.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="methodCard">
        <h3>Clashes, Liu Chong</h3>
        <p>Each animal sits directly across from one other on the wheel. That opposite is its clash, an energy aimed in the contrary direction. A clash is not a verdict, but it does ask for care, patience, and a willingness to translate.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="methodCard">
        <h3>Harms, Liu Hai</h3>
        <p>Six pairs carry a quieter strain, a harm that works slowly rather than loudly. Nothing breaks at once. The Oracle counts it as a small drag, the kind of friction worth naming early so it never gets to corrode.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="methodCard">
        <h3>Western elements</h3>
        <p>Each Sun sign carries Fire, Earth, Air, or Water. Shared elements feel the world the same way. Fire with Air and Earth with Water complement and feed each other. Fire with Water and Earth with Air run at different temperatures and need more bridging.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="methodCard">
        <h3>Modes</h3>
        <p>Signs also split into starters, sustainers, and shifters. Two different modes mean one person opens a thing and another keeps it alive. Two of the same mode can move as one or lock into a standoff, so the Oracle nudges the score either way.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE FIVE TIERS -->
  <section class="band" id="tiers">
    <p class="eyebrow">The five tiers</p>
    <h2>What each result means</h2>
    <p class="lede">Every match lands in one of five tiers. None of them is a sentence. The highest still has to be tended, and the hardest can become the most honest bond two people ever build.</p>

    <div class="tierGrid">
      <div class="tierCard">
        <span class="tierBadge tier-TwinFlame">Twin Flame</span>
        <p>The structure is rare and almost effortless. You recognize each other early and the recognition holds. The risk in a bond this easy is that you stop tending it, sure it will hold itself. It will not. Keep choosing each other on the ordinary days and this becomes the kind of love other people quietly study. The wheel opened the door. Walking through it daily is still yours to do.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tierCard">
        <span class="tierBadge tier-Strong">Strong</span>
        <p>The bones are good. You move at compatible speeds and your instincts mostly agree, which means your disagreements are about the world, not about each other. Trust that foundation enough to be honest inside it. A strong match rewards directness and grows dull under politeness. Say the true thing kindly and often, and this bond deepens for years rather than coasting on its early shine.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tierCard">
        <span class="tierBadge tier-Workable">Workable</span>
        <p>There is real ground here and a few honest gaps. Nothing carries you automatically, which is its own gift, because a workable match teaches both people how to choose. Name where your rhythms differ and build small agreements around them. Couples in this tier often outlast the effortless ones, precisely because they learned to do on purpose what the easy pairs were handed for free.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tierCard">
        <span class="tierBadge tier-Friction">Friction</span>
        <p>You pull in different directions, and that tension is not the same as doom. Friction can make heat or it can make wear. The difference is whether you treat the gap as a problem to win or a difference to respect. Slow down at the edges where you grind, get specific about what each of you actually needs, and let the contrast sharpen you both rather than divide you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tierCard">
        <span class="tierBadge tier-KarmicLesson">Karmic Lesson</span>
        <p>This is the hard, instructive kind of bond. Something in the pairing keeps handing each of you the exact lesson you came here to learn, usually through the other person. It can wound and it can free, sometimes both. A karmic match asks for unusual honesty, firm boundaries, and the humility to grow. Held well, it changes you. Held badly, it repeats. Go in with your eyes open.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="dim tierNote">A note that holds for every tier: the score reads the shape two natures make, not the choices two people make. Attention, honesty, and repair build a relationship. The wheel only tells you what raw material you are working with.</p>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <div class="brand">The Primal <b>Oracle</b></div>
    <p>Find your Primal Animal, read where you stand, and see who you match. Built on the fusion of the Chinese and Western zodiacs.</p>
    <p class="disclaimer">This is a tradition of meaning for reflection and entertainment. It is not medical, psychological, financial, or legal advice. The Primal Animal framework is adapted from the Primal Zodiac tradition. Stones and lunar practices are presented as cultural tradition, not as treatment.</p>
  </footer>

